    {
      "kind": "markup",
      "language": "markdown",
      "source": [
        "## Using the fs module",
        "",
        "You can list the entries of a directory using `readDirSync`. You can query file info with `statSync` (e.g the size of the file)",
        "This will return an iterator over the entries.",
        "",
        "",
        "Be sure to call it with a valid URI:",
        "* without a scheme a path is treated as a file path in system fs, can use relative path.",
        "* use the `file:` scheme for a directory in the system fs",
        "* use the `nngfile:` svheme for iGO filesystem paths, like `\"nngfile://app/ui_yugo\"` for example",
        "* everything before the `:` is a scheme unless it is a single letter in which case it is a windows drive letter",
        ""
      ]
    },
    {
      "kind": "code",
      "language": "xsmixed",
      "source": [
        "import * as fs from \"system://fs\"",
        "const dirFiles = +> fs.readDirSync(^).map(d => d.name);",
        "{}",
        "$log(...dirFiles(\"..\"))",
        ""
      ]
    },
    {
      "kind": "code",
